    <br>
    <h1>Truth Table Generator, version 0.1</h1>
    <p>Originally written in 2002, refreshed in 2013</p>
    <br>
    <p>This tools builds a truth table for your logic expression. Enter the expression you want to evaluate. See syntax guide below.</p>
    <br>
    <input type="text" onKeyDown="seeEvaluate()" id="expr" size="70">
    &nbsp; <input type="button" value="evaluate" onClick="evaluateMe()">
    <br>
    <br>
    <div id="logictable"></div>
    <br>
    <div id="results"></div>
    <br>
    <p>Use single lowercase letters as variables (e.g. <tt>w</tt>, <tt>x</tt>, <tt>g</tt>...).
    <br>
    Examples of syntax:</p>
    <pre>
    a+b ...... a or b
    ab ....... a and b
    a(b+c)d .. a and (b or c) and d
    a' ....... not a (either a backtick or a single quote will work)
    a'bc' .... (not a) and b and (not c)
    a^b ...... a xor b
    (ab)' .... not (a and b)</pre>
  </div>

